cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation. The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper proposes a novel loss function for optimizing linear constraints on the output space of a CNN, which could also place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The experiments involve extensive use of images, which could also suggest the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which could also place it in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
